  "helpFaq1Q": "I submitted a report but didn't get a token. What happened?",
  "helpFaq1A": "If the connection dropped before the confirmation loaded, your report may not have been saved. Please submit it again — duplicate reports are not a problem on our end.",
  "helpFaq2Q": "I lost my tracking token. Can I get it back?",
  "helpFaq2A": "If you provided contact info when reporting, the admin team can verify your identity and resend it. Otherwise, since ShieldNet stores no personal data by default, the token cannot be recovered.",
  "helpFaq3Q": "Will the harasser find out I reported them?",
  "helpFaq3A": "No. Reports are completely anonymous unless you choose to provide contact details, and that information is only ever visible to the admin team — never to the person you reported.",
  "helpFaq4Q": "Is my identity really anonymous?",
  "helpFaq4A": "Yes. By default we collect no name, account, or device identifier. The contact field is optional and used only for follow-up if you provide it.",
  "helpFaq5Q": "What happens to my evidence after I submit it?",
  "helpFaq5A": "Evidence is analyzed to help verify the report, then stored securely and used only for the takedown and review process.",
  "helpFaq6Q": "What if I need urgent help right now?",
  "helpFaq6A": "If you are in immediate danger, contact local emergency services first. For cyber harassment specifically, you can call the FIA Cybercrime Helpline at 1991 — see the emergency numbers above.",

